Here are some examples of the use of HarfPy ([GitLab](https://gitlab.com/ldo/harfpy),
[GitHub](https://github.com/ldo/harfpy)), my Python 3 binding for
[HarfBuzz](https://www.freedesktop.org/wiki/Software/HarfBuzz/). These scripts will also
need the following additional Python bindings:

* Qahirah ([GitLab](https://gitlab.com/ldo/qahirah),
  [GitHub](https://github.com/ldo/qahirah)) -- my binding for the
  [Cairo](https://www.cairographics.org/) graphics library
* python_freetype ([GitLab](https://gitlab.com/ldo/python_freetype),
  [GitHub](https://github.com/ldo/python_freetype)) -- my binding for
  [FreeType](https://www.freetype.org/)
* PyBidi ([GitLab](https://gitlab.com/ldo/pybidi),
  [GitHub](https://github.com/ldo/pybidi)) -- my binding for
  [FriBidi](https://fribidi.org/)

Some of them will give best results if your system has certain fonts installed-- see the
header comments for details.

Alternatively, you can see the generated output on my [DeviantArt
account](https://default-cube.deviantart.com/gallery/59919308/HarfPy-Examples).

Lawrence D'Oliveiro <ldo@geek-central.gen.nz>
